bead.description:
Wire the tenant_users M:N membership CRUD surface and the role-ceiling helper that caps credential issuance at the issuer's role. B1 already added the READ path (get_tenant_member); this bead adds the WRITE path plus the role-ceiling helper that C3 (credential issuance) depends on. This bead is parallel to B3 (federation) and they do not share files beyond the storage adapter trait.

## Scope — exactly what to add

### 1. Extend crates/axon-storage/src/adapter.rs StorageAdapter trait

Add two new methods alongside the B1 auth methods:

    /// Add or update a user's tenant membership. Idempotent on (tenant_id, user_id);
    /// if the row exists, the role is updated to the given value (this lets the
    /// same call act as both 'grant' and 'change role').
    ///
    /// ADR-018 §3 specifies tenant_users is keyed on (tenant_id, user_id). The
    /// SQL pattern is:
    ///   INSERT INTO tenant_users (tenant_id, user_id, role, added_at_ms)
    ///   VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)
    ///   ON CONFLICT (tenant_id, user_id) DO UPDATE SET role = excluded.role;
    fn upsert_tenant_member(
        &self,
        tenant_id: TenantId,
        user_id: UserId,
        role: TenantRole,
    ) -> Result<TenantMember, AxonError> {
        let _ = (tenant_id, user_id, role);
        Err(AxonError::Internal("upsert_tenant_member not supported by this adapter".into()))
    }

    /// Remove a user's tenant membership. Returns Ok(true) if a row was
    /// deleted, Ok(false) if no such membership existed.
    fn remove_tenant_member(
        &self,
        tenant_id: TenantId,
        user_id: UserId,
    ) -> Result<bool, AxonError> {
        let _ = (tenant_id, user_id);
        Ok(false)
    }

Default impls return Internal / false so unmigrated adapters are explicit about the gap.

### 2. Implement in all three storage backends

- crates/axon-storage/src/memory.rs — HashMap<(TenantId, UserId), TenantMember>; upsert overwrites.
- crates/axon-storage/src/sqlite.rs — rusqlite with the ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE SET role pattern.
- crates/axon-storage/src/postgres.rs — tokio_postgres with the same pattern.

### 3. Add role-ceiling helper to crates/axon-core/src/auth.rs

Add a method on TenantRole (or a free function, but a method is cleaner):

    impl TenantRole {
        /// The set of ops this role is allowed to delegate to a credential it
        /// issues. Per ADR-018 §4 grants rule table:
        ///   Admin → {Read, Write, Admin}
        ///   Write → {Read, Write}       (cannot delegate Admin)
        ///   Read  → {Read}
        pub const fn delegable_ops(self) -> &'static [Op] {
            match self {
                TenantRole::Admin => &[Op::Read, Op::Write, Op::Admin],
                TenantRole::Write => &[Op::Read, Op::Write],
                TenantRole::Read  => &[Op::Read],
            }
        }

        /// Check if this role can delegate a single op.
        pub fn can_delegate(self, op: Op) -> bool {
            self.delegable_ops().contains(&op)
        }

        /// Check if a requested grants set is wholly within this role's ceiling.
        /// Returns Err(AuthError::GrantsExceedRole) with detail if any requested
        /// op on any database is outside the ceiling.
        pub fn enforce_ceiling(self, grants: &Grants) -> Result<(), AuthError> {
            for db in &grants.databases {
                for op in &db.ops {
                    if !self.can_delegate(*op) {
                        return Err(AuthError::GrantsExceedRole);
                    }
                }
            }
            Ok(())
        }
    }

Note: A2 already introduced can_delegate as a method on TenantRole — if it exists, REUSE it. Do not duplicate. Your job may be to add delegable_ops and enforce_ceiling alongside the existing can_delegate.

## Required: add GrantsExceedRole to the AuthError enum if it is not present

A2 landed AuthError with 14 variants matching the ADR-018 §4 HTTP failure table. GrantsExceedRole is NOT in that table — it is a control-plane credential-issuance error, not a data-plane HTTP failure. So either:

(a) Add GrantsExceedRole as a 15th variant and update AUTH_ERROR_VARIANT_COUNT to 15, plus the exhaustive match. This is the clean option.

(b) Return a different error type from enforce_ceiling — e.g. a new CredentialIssuanceError enum in axon-core.

Choose (a) — keep everything in AuthError, bump the variant count, update status_code() to return 403 for GrantsExceedRole, and update error_code() to return "grants_exceed_role". ADR-018 §4 says the control-plane route returns 403 grants_exceed_role so this is consistent with the table even though the row isn't in the data-plane matrix.

Update locations:
- crates/axon-core/src/auth.rs: add the variant, update the compile-time exhaustive match, bump AUTH_ERROR_VARIANT_COUNT from 14 to 15, update status_code() and error_code().
- crates/axon-core/src/auth.rs: the auth_error_display test, the auth_error_status_and_code_coverage test, and any assertion on variant count — all need updating.

### 4. Tests

#### crates/axon-storage/tests/tenant_users_test.rs (NEW)

Postgres testcontainers + SQLite in-memory, following the auth_schema.rs test pattern:

a) upsert_fresh_creates_membership — fresh DB, upsert(tenant_id, user_id, Write), assert 1 row in tenant_users with role=write.
b) upsert_same_pair_updates_role — upsert the same pair with a different role, assert 1 row with the new role.
c) remove_existing_returns_true — upsert, then remove, assert returns true and 0 rows.
d) remove_missing_returns_false — remove a never-inserted pair, assert returns false.
e) get_tenant_member_after_upsert — verifies the B1 read path finds the row after the new write path creates it.

Run across memory, sqlite (in-memory), and postgres (testcontainers with skip-if-no-docker fallback from the existing pattern).

#### crates/axon-core/src/auth.rs unit tests (ADD to the existing tests module)

f) delegable_ops_admin — assert Admin.delegable_ops() == [Read, Write, Admin]
g) delegable_ops_write — assert Write.delegable_ops() == [Read, Write]; explicitly assert Admin NOT in the set
h) delegable_ops_read — assert Read.delegable_ops() == [Read]
i) enforce_ceiling_admin_accepts_any — proptest: random Grants with ops in {Read, Write, Admin}; Admin.enforce_ceiling(&grants) always returns Ok
j) enforce_ceiling_write_rejects_admin_ops — proptest: random Grants where at least one database has Admin in ops; Write.enforce_ceiling(&grants) returns Err(GrantsExceedRole)
k) enforce_ceiling_read_rejects_write_or_admin — proptest: random Grants with any non-Read op; Read.enforce_ceiling(&grants) returns Err(GrantsExceedRole)

Use proptest with prop_oneof! for TenantRole strategies and Just(Op::X) combinators for Op strategies — not fixed string arrays (see A2 iter 3 review notes; fixed strategies are behaviorally unit tests and don't exercise property coverage).

PROP-009 is the name for the full property test; it lives in this file.

### 5. AUTH_ERROR_VARIANT_COUNT and exhaustive match update

If you add GrantsExceedRole (recommended): update the const _: () = { match AuthError { ... } } exhaustive check at the bottom of crates/axon-core/src/auth.rs to include the new variant, and update AUTH_ERROR_VARIANT_COUNT from 14 to 15. Also update the auth_error_variant_count_is_14 test name and body to use 15.

## Context you must know

### Already landed
- A1: users, user_identities, tenant_users tables with correct schema (tenant_users has (tenant_id, user_id) composite PK, role TEXT NOT NULL, added_at_ms INTEGER NOT NULL).
- A2: TenantRole enum { Admin, Write, Read }, Op enum { Read, Write, Admin }, Grants/GrantedDatabase structs, AuthError with 14 variants + AUTH_ERROR_VARIANT_COUNT compile-time assert.
- B1: StorageAdapter::get_tenant_member (READ path) — B4 adds the WRITE path.
- B2: AuthError → HTTP mapping via status_code/error_code + IntoResponse — B4's new GrantsExceedRole variant needs these extended.

### Files to touch

- crates/axon-storage/src/adapter.rs — add upsert_tenant_member + remove_tenant_member trait methods
- crates/axon-storage/src/memory.rs — impl
- crates/axon-storage/src/sqlite.rs — impl
- crates/axon-storage/src/postgres.rs — impl
- crates/axon-core/src/auth.rs — add GrantsExceedRole variant + bump count + exhaustive match + delegable_ops + enforce_ceiling + unit tests
- crates/axon-storage/tests/tenant_users_test.rs — NEW test file

## Files NOT to touch

- crates/axon-server/src/auth_pipeline.rs — B1's pipeline; B4 provides the helper but does not yet wire it into the credential issuance endpoint (that's C3)
- crates/axon-server/src/auth.rs — legacy Tailscale path, leave alone
- crates/axon-server/src/federation.rs — B3's territory; if it exists by the time you read this, do not modify it

## Verification

    cargo test -p axon-core  # delegable_ops tests + PROP-009 proptest
    cargo test -p axon-storage  # tenant_users_test (memory + sqlite + postgres)
    cargo test -p axon-server --test auth_rejection_matrix  # must still pass with updated variant count
    cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings  # must be clean
